The YouTube videos in the "Critical Skills" section have been updated to play inline within the application.

**Changes Implemented:**
1.  **Inline Playback**: The video thumbnails are now interactive. Clicking on a video card replaces the thumbnail with an embedded YouTube player (`iframe`), allowing the user to watch the video directly on the page.
2.  **"Watch on YouTube" Option**: A link has been added below the video (and as a tooltip icon) to allow opening the video in a new tab on YouTube, satisfying the requirement to still have this option available.
3.  **Component Restructuring**: A `VideoCard` component was extracted within `CriticalSkills.tsx` to manage the playing state for each video independently.

**Files Modified:**
-   `src/components/CriticalSkills.tsx`: Refactored to use the new `VideoCard` component with embedded playback logic.

**Testing:**
-   Created a temporary test page to verify the video player functionality in isolation.
-   Confirmed via screenshots that clicking the "Play" button (or thumbnail) successfully loads the video player inline.
-   Verified the presence of the "YouTube" external link.

The application now supports seamless video consumption without forcing users to leave the site, while retaining the original external link functionality.
